An institution is required to carry out customer due diligence to prevent money laundering and terrorist financing in the following instances:
- when establishing a business relationship, i.e. a relationship which pertains to the institution's professional activities and which is expected to continue for some time;
- when carrying out one or more transactions on behalf of a client for a total amount of at least EUR 15,000;
- when there are indications that the client is involved in money laundering or terrorist financing;

- when there are doubts about the reliability of previously obtained data on the client; or when there is cause to do so by reason of a risk that an existing client has become involved in money laundering or terrorist financing.
